name: Database Design Class
des: Database design is the organization of data according to a database model. The designer determines what data must be stored and how the data elements interrelate.

name: Cloud Computing Class
des: Cloud computing is the on-demand availability of computer system resources, especially data storage and computing power, without direct active management by the user.

name: Networking Class
des: Computer networking refers to interconnected computing devices that can exchange data and share resources with each other.

name: Structural Programming Class
des: Structured programming (sometimes known as modular programming) is a programming paradigm that facilitates the creation of programs with readable code and reusable components.

name: Physics Class
des: Physics is the natural science that studies matter, its fundamental constituents, its motion and behavior through space and time, and the related entities of energy and force.

name: Mathmatics Class
des: Mathematics is the science and study of quality, structure, space, and change. Mathematicians seek out patterns, formulate new conjectures.

name: English Class
des: The English language is an Indo-European language in the West Germanic language group. Modern English is widely considered to be the lingua franca of the world and is the standard language in a wide variety of fields

name: EEE Class
des: Electrical engineering is an engineering discipline concerned with the study, design, and application of equipment, devices, and systems

name: Hardware Design Class
des: Hardware design involves, design of computer hardware components, including circuit boards, microchips, schematics and scanners.
